
To move forward in the selection process, you will be expected to complete an assessment.

For this assessment you will be asked to create an OS image with the requirements below.

 

Create an installable Debian/Linux 12 image to an x86_64 hardware. (Example: an iso image). 
1) Use Bitbake/Yocto based tool to achieve.
2) Enable secure boot with the ability to use custom keys
3) Create a full disk encryption with LUKS partition and disk unlock password bind to TPM
4) Allow user to SSH (protocol)
5) Implement SWUpdate for OS update
 

You will have until the end of the weekend to complete this assessment and submit for Amazon to review. Please provide us a workable image as well as the build package.
